                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d187">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-11-28T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 28, 1930—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>13. Your 39, 40, 41, 42, of November 26, your 44 of November 27 and your No. 45
                    of November 28.<note n="88" xml:id="d187fn88">Nos. 40, 41, 42, and 44 not
                        printed.</note> Department approves of texts as telegraphed on the clear
                    understanding that such approval does not prejudice its attitude at the final
                    conference, when figures are under discussion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
